=========================================================
IDENTITY & ACCESS MODULE - USER, ROLE, PERMISSION SYSTEM
=========================================================

1. DATABASE TABLES
------------------
The Identity module manages 6 tables:

- users: Stores all user accounts (id, public_id, first_name, last_name, email, phone, password_hash, status, etc.)
- roles: Defines roles (super_admin, store_admin, manager, cashier, driver, customer)
- permissions: Defines granular permissions (catalog.manage, orders.manage, etc.)
- role_permissions: Many-to-many linking roles to permissions
- user_roles: Many-to-many linking users to roles
- user_sessions: Tracks user login sessions with token hashes

2. HOW PERMISSIONS WORK (Hierarchy)
-----------------------------------
Users -> Roles -> Permissions

- A User can have MULTIPLE Roles (via user_roles table)
- A Role can have MULTIPLE Permissions (via role_permissions table)
- Permissions are inherited through roles

Example:
  User "John" has role "manager"
  Role "manager" has permission "orders.manage"
  => John can manage orders

  User "Jane" has roles "manager" + "cashier"
  Role "cashier" has permission "pos.sell"
  => Jane can manage orders AND create POS sales

3. SEEDED DEFAULT DATA
----------------------
Default Roles (seeded by IdentityDatabaseSeeder):
  1. super_admin  - Full system access
  2. store_admin  - Store administration access
  3. manager      - Store manager access
  4. cashier      - POS cashier access
  5. driver       - Delivery driver access
  6. customer     - Customer account access

Default Permissions (seeded by IdentityDatabaseSeeder):
  1. catalog.manage  - Create and update catalog items
  2. orders.manage   - Manage orders
  3. orders.refund   - Process refunds
  4. pos.sell        - Create POS sales
  5. delivery.manage - Manage deliveries
  6. settings.manage - Manage application settings
  7. reports.view    - View business reports

4. UI MANAGEMENT (via Sidebar)
-------------------------------
The sidebar has "Identity & Access" section (after Dashboard) with:
  - Users:    /users    (CRUD with DataTable)
  - Roles:    /roles    (CRUD with DataTable, can assign permissions)
  - Permissions: /permissions (CRUD with DataTable)

All routes are under auth+verified middleware.

5. MODULE INTEGRATION
---------------------
All modules that reference User now use: Modules\Identity\Models\User

Files Updated:
  - config/auth.php                          (auth model)
  - Modules/Store/app/Models/StoreStaff.php  (user relationship)
  - Modules/Store/app/Models/Address.php     (user relationship)
  - Modules/Inventory/app/Models/InventoryMovement.php (createdBy relationship)
  - app/Http/Controllers/Auth/RegisteredUserController.php
  - app/Http/Controllers/Auth/NewPasswordController.php
  - app/Http/Requests/ProfileUpdateRequest.php
  - database/factories/UserFactory.php
  - database/seeders/DatabaseSeeder.php

6. MODULE MIGRATION ORDER
--------------------------
Since Identity module has priority=1, it will be migrated FIRST,
before Store, Catalog, Inventory, and other modules that depend on users.

Migration files ordered:
  000001 - create_users_table
  000002 - create_roles_table
  000003 - create_permissions_table
  000004 - create_role_permissions_table
  000005 - create_user_roles_table
  000006 - create_user_sessions_table

7. ROLE-PERMISSION ASSIGNMENT EXAMPLE
--------------------------------------
Creating a new role "manager" with permissions:
  POST /roles
  {
    "name": "manager",
    "description": "Store manager",
    "permissions": [1, 2, 3]  // Array of permission IDs
  }

This uses RoleService.saveRole() which syncs permissions:
  $role->permissions()->sync($data['permissions']);

8. VERIFYING USER PERMISSIONS (Usage in Code)
----------------------------------------------
To check if a user has a permission:
  $user->roles()->whereHas('permissions', function($q) {
      $q->where('name', 'orders.manage');
  })->exists();

Or check if user has a specific role:
  $user->roles()->where('name', 'manager')->exists();

9. SIDEBAR NAVIGATION ORDER
----------------------------
1. Dashboard
2. Identity & Access (NEW - Users, Roles, Permissions)
3. Catalog (Products, Categories, Brands)
4. Store & Location (Stores, Staff, Countries, Addresses, Settings)
5. Inventory (Stock, Locations, Movements)
6. Orders (Order List, Returns)
7. Delivery (Shipments, Drivers)
8. POS (Registers, Sales)
9. Reports
10. Settings